# Entity cache
- Wrapper around CacheAPI in the browser
- Allows the lookup/storage of Drupal entities in JS

### Details
- Cache API stores based on request (path)
- entity_cache passes an ID with optional config
`let entity = new entityCache(id, type, path)`
- Parameters
-- id : some type of unique id (eg. sku, nid, uuid)
-- type : type of request to process
--- direct : if the id is a path to be called (path is not needed)
--- parameter : adds id to the end of the path
--- jsonapi : inserts id into a standard Drupal jsonapi request
- Methods
-- entity.data (raw JSON)
-- entity.update() (delete and recreate)
-- entity.delete()
